// DiffView (ai-ui display)
// Renders a side-by-side or unified text diff using react-diff-viewer-continued.
// Provides a toggle to switch between split and unified view modes.
// Shows "No changes detected" when before === after.

FUNCTION DiffView(before, after, fileName, mode, contextLines, language, fullHeight, ...) -> JSX  EXPORT
  Manages currentMode state (split|unified), defaulting to the mode prop.
  Detects system dark/light mode for theme.
  IF before === after: renders a "No changes detected" placeholder.
  ELSE: renders header (fileName, language badge, split/unified toggle)
  + DiffViewer (from react-diff-viewer-continued) + summary footer
  (Additions/Removals legend).
  IF fullHeight: container fills available height via flex-1; ELSE uses max-h-96.
